# GE Agent Factory — root env (loaded by the `ge` CLI / `make` targets run
# from the repo root; Bun auto-loads a `.env` file from the process cwd).
#
# Local mode (see SETUP.md steps 1–5) needs none of this — it runs with no
# cloud credentials. These are the FOUNDATIONAL vars shared by cloud-facing
# tooling (the `ge` CLI, `make bootstrap`/`provision`) AND by both apps
# (apps/console, apps/presentation), so they're collected once here instead
# of being duplicated in every app's own .env.example.
#
# This file is intentionally NOT a full aggregator: each app has its own,
# larger set of app-specific vars (provisioning flags, Firebase/auth config,
# Vite build-time defaults, etc.) that only matter when running that app.
# Copy this file to `.env` at the repo root for CLI/cloud-ops use, THEN also
# copy the relevant app's own template if you're running that app:
#   - apps/console/.env.example      -> apps/console/.env
#   - apps/presentation/.env.example -> apps/presentation/.env

# --- Shared: GCP project (required for any cloud-facing command) ---------
# The GCP project used by the `ge` CLI, Vertex/Discovery API calls, and both
# apps' read paths. Falls back to `gcloud config get-value project` / the
# local ge config file if unset here — but setting it explicitly avoids
# surprises when multiple projects are configured on your machine.
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=my-gcp-project-id

# GCP region for regional resources (Cloud Run, etc). Optional — most
# commands have a sane default (see each app's own .env.example).
# GCP_REGION=us-central1

# --- Shared: Gemini Enterprise (required only for `make bootstrap`/cloud provisioning) ---
# projects/<num>/locations/global/collections/default_collection/engines/<app>
# See SETUP.md step 6 (Optional: Cloud setup) for how this is used.
# GEMINI_ENTERPRISE_APP_ID=
